00:30:07,197 --> 00:30:09,532
-I don't know you.
-Oh, well, I'm very famous.

750
00:30:09,616 --> 00:30:11,451
I perform for crown heads of Europe.

751
00:30:11,535 --> 00:30:13,744
And the rest of their bodies
if they're still attached.

752
00:30:13,828 --> 00:30:16,581
I have met the queen.
She matched me drink for drink,

753
00:30:16,665 --> 00:30:18,207
and then we… [LAUGHS]

754
00:30:18,291 --> 00:30:21,210
Slippery stool here.
Now, wouldn't that be a story?

755
00:30:21,294 --> 00:30:23,838
Cause of death: slippery barstool.

756
00:30:23,922 --> 00:30:26,257
Not a manly death like fighting in a war

757
00:30:26,341 --> 00:30:27,967
-or choking on steak.
-Christ.

758
00:30:28,051 --> 00:30:31,179
Take a card.
I'm a pacifist and a vegetarian,

759
00:30:31,263 --> 00:30:33,973
so I guess it's the
deadly barstool for me.

760
00:30:34,057 --> 00:30:35,475
Put it back.

761
00:30:35,559 --> 00:30:37,185
[EXHALES]

762
00:30:37,269 --> 00:30:38,603
Ooh.

763
00:30:38,687 --> 00:30:40,605
-This your card?
-Shit. Yeah.

764
00:30:40,689 --> 00:30:42,356
-Whiskey neat.
-You're picking those up.

765
00:30:42,440 --> 00:30:44,609
Think of a number. I guess right,

766
00:30:44,693 --> 00:30:46,194
-you pick up the cards.
-[CHUCKLES]

767
00:30:46,278 --> 00:30:48,654
-Fucking hate magicians.
-Oh, that's just Alfie.

768
00:30:48,738 --> 00:30:51,199
-He's a regular.
-Yeah, well, if he tries to pull

769
00:30:51,283 --> 00:30:53,784
a quarter out of my nose, I'm
gonna jam a rabbit up his ass.

770
00:30:53,868 --> 00:30:55,703
-Shit.
-Pick a card.

771
00:30:55,787 --> 00:30:57,455
I guess right, you buy me a drink.

772
00:30:57,539 --> 00:30:59,582
-Maybe some other time.
-Oh, bad day?

773
00:30:59,666 --> 00:31:01,751
-Wow. You are magic.
-Here.

774
00:31:01,835 --> 00:31:03,794
Just for fun. Which hand?

775
00:31:03,878 --> 00:31:05,505
-What am I, six?
-For fun.

776
00:31:05,589 --> 00:31:06,881
Get your mind off things.

777
00:31:06,965 --> 00:31:08,716
That one. I watched you pick it up.

778
00:31:08,800 --> 00:31:10,801
Which hand? For fun.

779
00:31:10,885 --> 00:31:12,803
I know you're having enough
trouble finding money as it is,

780
00:31:12,887 --> 00:31:14,096
-right?
-What?

781
00:31:14,180 --> 00:31:15,682
Which hand?

782
00:31:16,933 --> 00:31:18,518
Two out of three. Which hand?

783
00:31:18,602 --> 00:31:20,269
-Wait, that was two out of three.
-Three out of four.

784
00:31:20,353 --> 00:31:22,313
Just for fun.
Can't let you go up in smoke,

785
00:31:22,397 --> 00:31:23,564
-right?
-Hey, how did you…

786
00:31:23,648 --> 00:31:26,067
-Pick a hand.
-I'm gonna be fucking wrong!

787
00:31:26,151 --> 00:31:28,444
-Have a little faith.
-BARTENDER: Alfie, come on.

788
00:31:28,528 --> 00:31:30,446
I was trying to let you win.

789
00:31:30,530 --> 00:31:33,783
Look, pal, screw with someone else, huh?

790
00:31:39,831 --> 00:31:43,251
You know, it's not good to sit
in a bar when you're depressed.

791
00:31:43,335 --> 00:31:44,627
He's gonna keep talking to me.

792
00:31:44,711 --> 00:31:46,170
Sometimes it's good to be somewhere

793
00:31:46,254 --> 00:31:47,380
that makes you smile.

794
00:31:47,464 --> 00:31:48,839
Alfie.

795
00:31:48,923 --> 00:31:51,676
Where would you like to be right now?

796
00:31:51,760 --> 00:31:54,178
-Fucking place but here.
-ALFIE: Hmm.

797
00:31:54,262 --> 00:31:57,139
What's the opposite of here?

798
00:31:57,223 --> 00:31:59,016
How about… here?

799
00:31:59,100 --> 00:32:01,102
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

800
00:32:03,605 --> 00:32:05,982
What the fuck?

801
00:32:06,983 --> 00:32:08,609
[FINGERS SNAP]

802
00:32:08,693 --> 00:32:10,570
What the hell just happened?

803
00:32:10,654 --> 00:32:12,196
You just bought him a drink.

804
00:32:12,280 --> 00:32:16,450
<i>-♪ I'm so lonesome… ♪</i>
-Fucking hate magicians.

805
00:32:16,534 --> 00:32:19,287
[THE BARRY SISTERS "CONEY ISLAND"]

806
00:32:19,371 --> 00:32:23,833
<i>♪ Harvey mentioned his
home, a tropical town ♪</i>

807
00:32:23,917 --> 00:32:25,919
[SINGING IN YIDDISH]

808
00:32:33,301 --> 00:32:35,803
<i>-♪ In Coney Island ♪
-♪ In Coney Island ♪</i>

809
00:32:35,887 --> 00:32:37,722
[SINGING IN YIDDISH]

810
00:32:37,806 --> 00:32:40,808
<i>-♪ In Coney Island ♪
-♪ In Coney Island… ♪</i>

811
00:32:40,892 --> 00:32:42,518
ABE: Everyone stay together.

812
00:32:42,602 --> 00:32:45,438
-Oh, boys, look.
-It's not a real mermaid.

813
00:32:45,522 --> 00:32:47,530
She sold us pickles earlier. Keep moving.

814
00:32:47,614 --> 00:32:47,774
Hi.

815
00:32:47,858 --> 00:32:49,358
Boy, Abe, are you fun.

816
00:32:49,442 --> 00:32:52,111
This wasn't supposed to
be an all-day outing, Moishe.

817
00:32:52,195 --> 00:32:55,489
Stop that. The agreement was
one ride on the Wonder Wheel,

818
00:32:55,573 --> 00:32:56,824
then home. Stop that.

819
00:32:56,908 --> 00:32:59,535
It did not include the
whole of Coney Island.

820
00:32:59,619 --> 00:33:02,747
Stop that. We have now been
heading toward the Wonder Wheel

821
00:33:02,831 --> 00:33:04,290
for a full two hours.

822
00:33:04,374 --> 00:33:06,751
We've stopped for games and T-shirts

823
00:33:06,835 --> 00:33:09,211
and funny pictures of
us sticking our heads

824
00:33:09,295 --> 00:33:12,006
through cutouts of
bodybuilders and cowboys.

825
00:33:12,090 --> 00:33:14,592
I mean it. It's time we do

826
00:33:14,676 --> 00:33:16,802
-what we came here for already.
-SHIRLEY: Look what I got!

827
00:33:16,886 --> 00:33:19,513
Here we go! <i>♪ I scream, you scream ♪</i>

828
00:33:19,597 --> 00:33:21,098
<i>♪ We all scream for ice cream ♪</i>

829
00:33:21,182 --> 00:33:23,017
-ABE: Oh, for the love of God.
-For Jacob

830
00:33:23,101 --> 00:33:26,437
-and Petey and Moishe and Joely.
-Thank you.

831
00:33:26,521 --> 00:33:28,564
We've come to a dead stop here, Shirley.

832
00:33:28,648 --> 00:33:30,399
And for Rose and for me.

833
00:33:30,483 --> 00:33:33,152
We can give out ice cream
and walk at the same time,

834
00:33:33,236 --> 00:33:33,507
can't we?

835
00:33:33,591 --> 00:33:34,487
-ETHAN: Grandma, Grandma.
-And finally…

836
00:33:34,571 --> 00:33:36,113
Oh, the birthday boy.

837
00:33:36,197 --> 00:33:37,782
By the time we get there…

838
00:33:37,866 --> 00:33:40,117
-Wait, no ice cream for me?
-You don't eat ice cream.

839
00:33:40,201 --> 00:33:42,203
You don't eat anything,
and she got you one.

840
00:33:42,287 --> 00:33:43,663
I got to get something to drink.

841
00:33:43,747 --> 00:33:45,039
We'll lose the others.

842
00:33:45,123 --> 00:33:47,083
Oh, they'll be back.

843
00:33:48,460 --> 00:33:50,211
You know, I <i>schtupped</i> your mother

844
00:33:50,295 --> 00:33:51,587
under this very boardwalk.

845
00:33:51,671 --> 00:33:52,963
Thank you for that.

846
00:33:53,047 --> 00:33:55,007
Just thought you'd
like a little family history.

847
00:33:55,091 --> 00:33:56,926
-Two.
-VENDOR: You got it.

848
00:33:58,094 --> 00:33:59,845
Everything okay at the club?

849
00:33:59,929 --> 00:34:01,889
Fine. Why would you say that?

850
00:34:01,973 --> 00:34:04,016
You got a look all Maisel men get

851
00:34:04,100 --> 00:34:06,519
when they got work
troubles or prostate issues.

852
00:34:06,603 --> 00:34:09,814
I just… got these landlords,

853
00:34:09,898 --> 00:34:11,774
and they're a little upset with me.

854
00:34:11,858 --> 00:34:13,984
-Why?
-The club's drawing too much attention

855
00:34:14,068 --> 00:34:15,236
to their other business.

856
00:34:15,320 --> 00:34:17,530
-You know, downstairs?
-Ah, yes.

857
00:34:17,614 --> 00:34:19,198
I can't be at war with these people.

858
00:34:19,282 --> 00:34:20,783
For many reasons.

859
00:34:20,867 --> 00:34:22,743
-Then you got to pay 'em.
-I do pay them.

860
00:34:22,827 --> 00:34:25,037
Not rent, you <i>yutz.</i>
<i>Payola.</i> Give 'em a taste.

861
00:34:25,121 --> 00:34:26,622
I don't think that's
what they're looking for.

862
00:34:26,706 --> 00:34:28,791
Of course it is.
There's not a thing in the world

863
00:34:28,875 --> 00:34:31,043
that money can't fix. You see your son?

864
00:34:31,127 --> 00:34:33,129
Had a fit to win that Popeye doll

865
00:34:33,213 --> 00:34:34,839
at the whack-a-mole game back there.

866
00:34:34,923 --> 00:34:37,299
You think he's really such a
terrific whack-a-mole player?

867
00:34:37,383 --> 00:34:39,510
You saw him.
All he hit was the kid next to him.

868
00:34:39,594 --> 00:34:41,011
I slip the guy five bucks,

869
00:34:41,095 --> 00:34:43,264
suddenly, Ethan's the
king of whack-a-mole.

870
00:34:43,348 --> 00:34:45,141
Five bucks. Got the doll.
What did we learn?

871
00:34:45,225 --> 00:34:47,435
Nothing.
Including how to play whack-a-mole.

872
00:34:47,519 --> 00:34:49,437
ROSE: Abe, please. It was an accident.

873
00:34:49,521 --> 00:34:51,856
You saw we took a wrong
turn and said nothing.

874
00:34:51,940 --> 00:34:55,025
And now we have to double
back around the Parachute Jump,

875
00:34:55,109 --> 00:34:57,195
and if we get vomited on from the sky,

876
00:34:57,279 --> 00:34:58,613
it's on your head. Stop that.

877
00:34:58,697 --> 00:35:00,365
This is a wonderful camera, Mr. Weissman.

878
00:35:00,449 --> 00:35:01,616
I'm glad you like it. Keep up.

879
00:35:01,700 --> 00:35:03,285
I got beautiful shots of the boardwalk

880
00:35:03,369 --> 00:35:05,078
and the ocean and very funny pony rides.

881
00:35:05,162 --> 00:35:06,997
-Double-time, double-time.
-I was thinking

882
00:35:07,081 --> 00:35:09,541
-we could get one all together?
-Absolutely not.

883
00:35:09,625 --> 00:35:11,334
Hello. We need, uh…

884
00:35:11,418 --> 00:35:13,462
Did you boys bring any money from home?

885
00:35:13,546 --> 00:35:15,797
No? Great. Guess I'm paying.

886
00:35:15,881 --> 00:35:19,259
<i>♪ At the seashore, by the tropical</i> ♪

887
00:35:19,343 --> 00:35:20,594
[SINGING IN YIDDISH]

888
00:35:20,678 --> 00:35:22,680
BOY: Joey!

889
00:35:24,557 --> 00:35:27,893
Joey!

890
00:35:27,977 --> 00:35:29,603
Tell your parents I'll give
them ten percent of the take.

891
00:35:29,687 --> 00:35:30,937
-MEI: <i>Joel…</i>
-Just tell 'em.

892
00:35:31,021 --> 00:35:32,564
First of all, I never said
they were my parents,

893
00:35:32,648 --> 00:35:34,441
and second of all, this
wasn't a shakedown.

894
00:35:34,525 --> 00:35:35,817
Whatever it is, that's the deal.

895
00:35:35,901 --> 00:35:37,694
<i>I'll tell them five and let them say ten.</i>

896
00:35:37,778 --> 00:35:38,820
You're just so much more successful

897
00:35:38,904 --> 00:35:40,280
than you were supposed to be.

898
00:35:40,364 --> 00:35:43,074
So, now that your search
and destroy mission is over…

899
00:35:43,158 --> 00:35:44,493
It wasn't a search and destroy mission.

900
00:35:44,577 --> 00:35:45,702
Just a destroy mission.

901
00:35:45,786 --> 00:35:46,828
Now that it's over,

902
00:35:46,912 --> 00:35:48,580
you still gonna be coming around?

903
00:35:48,664 --> 00:35:49,956
Yes.

904
00:35:50,040 --> 00:35:52,626
A lot. Too much.

905
00:35:52,710 --> 00:35:54,669
<i>It makes you feel any better,
the rent they're charging you</i>

906
00:35:54,753 --> 00:35:56,213
<i>-is really low.</i>
-That's something.

907
00:35:56,297 --> 00:35:57,798
They will be raising
it next year, however.

908
00:35:57,882 --> 00:35:59,800
It will be ridiculously high and unfair.

909
00:35:59,884 --> 00:36:01,927
Terrific. I'll see you tonight?

910
00:36:02,011 --> 00:36:04,596
Yes.
I'll be in my rent collector's outfit.

911
00:36:04,680 --> 00:36:07,057
If anyone can pull it off, it's you.

912
00:36:07,141 --> 00:36:09,476
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

913
00:36:09,560 --> 00:36:12,646
VENDOR: Pretzels! Get your pretzels!

914
00:36:12,730 --> 00:36:15,733
Get your pretzels! Pretzels!

915
00:36:28,078 --> 00:36:30,914
It's short. He owes me a dollar.
You owe me a dollar!

916
00:36:30,998 --> 00:36:33,083
Abe, either go over to
the booth and discuss it

917
00:36:33,167 --> 00:36:34,918
or accept that he owes you a dollar.

918
00:36:35,002 --> 00:36:37,879
But if I go over there,
you will all follow,

919
00:36:37,963 --> 00:36:39,965
-and I will never get this… Stop that.
-[SHUTTER CLICKS]

920
00:36:40,049 --> 00:36:42,425
I will never get this
train back on the tracks.

921
00:36:42,509 --> 00:36:44,386
-Who wants some funnel cake?
-Shirley, no.

922
00:36:44,470 --> 00:36:45,679
-BOYS: Me!
-Say cheese!

923
00:36:45,763 --> 00:36:47,430
Zelda, please.
I'm gonna take that camera back.

924
00:36:47,514 --> 00:36:49,140
Abe, I have to make a call at 3:00,

925
00:36:49,224 --> 00:36:51,309
so we either have to be
done with the ride by then,

926
00:36:51,393 --> 00:36:53,687
-or we should wait until after.
-Who are you calling?

927
00:36:53,771 --> 00:36:56,606
It's a potential client,
if you must know.

928
00:36:56,690 --> 00:36:59,192
Is this that matchmaking business again?

929
00:36:59,276 --> 00:37:01,111
I… I have to tell you, I don't get it.

930
00:37:01,195 --> 00:37:03,280
Well, you don't have to get it.
Only I have to get it.

931
00:37:03,364 --> 00:37:05,657
How lazy are people anyway?

932
00:37:05,741 --> 00:37:08,410
I mean, they can't just
find spouses on their own?

933
00:37:08,494 --> 00:37:10,453
-You didn't.
-Of course I did.

934
00:37:10,537 --> 00:37:12,664
I met you through a family friend. Sonja.

935
00:37:12,748 --> 00:37:14,708
Yes, Sonja the matchmaker.

936
00:37:14,792 --> 00:37:16,877
-MIDGE: Mama!
-Miriam.

937
00:37:16,961 --> 00:37:18,211
ETHAN: Mommy!

938
00:37:18,295 --> 00:37:20,297
I heard someone had
an unexpected birthday.

939
00:37:20,381 --> 00:37:22,340
-What are you doing here?
-You said you were

940
00:37:22,424 --> 00:37:24,718
-in Prague.
-I did, yes.

941
00:37:24,802 --> 00:37:24,973
But…

942
00:37:25,057 --> 00:37:26,845
Explain later.
Everyone, on the cars. Now.

943
00:37:26,929 --> 00:37:28,305
Why aren't you on tour?

944
00:37:28,389 --> 00:37:30,056
Why'd you let them
change our son's birthday?

945
00:37:30,140 --> 00:37:31,266
-It was out of my control.
-Same here.

946
00:37:31,350 --> 00:37:32,726
I wish you'd told me
you were coming back.

947
00:37:32,810 --> 00:37:34,019
We could've moved
his birthday to tomorrow.

948
00:37:34,103 --> 00:37:35,812
I was actually hoping
I could talk to you all

949
00:37:35,896 --> 00:37:37,480
about what happened.
Maybe we could go somewhere…

950
00:37:37,564 --> 00:37:39,900
No time. Rose, move.
Shirley, go with Rose. Oh.

951
00:37:39,984 --> 00:37:41,818
-MIDGE: But… But, Papa, I…
-Miriam,

952
00:37:41,902 --> 00:37:43,528
we'll pay attention to you later.

953
00:37:43,612 --> 00:37:45,530
Ethan, go. Joel, go. Moishe, go.

954
00:37:45,614 --> 00:37:46,903
If I could just talk to you for a minute.

955
00:37:46,987 --> 00:37:47,575
ABE: Sorry. Jacob.

956
00:37:47,659 --> 00:37:50,368
-Petey, go. Zelda, come.
-ZELDA: I want to stay here

957
00:37:50,452 --> 00:37:51,143
and take pictures.

958
00:37:51,227 --> 00:37:52,203
-Papa, please.
-ABE: Oh.

959
00:37:52,287 --> 00:37:55,624
Miriam, um… Return this for me.

960
00:37:55,708 --> 00:37:58,001
Mention that he shorted me a dollar.
Don't press it.

961
00:37:58,085 --> 00:37:59,753
I'm not threatening legal action.

962
00:37:59,837 --> 00:38:01,922
But if there is someone official around,

963
00:38:02,006 --> 00:38:05,258
complain in a very loud
voice, then cry and faint.

964
00:38:05,342 --> 00:38:07,093
But… Wait. Wait!

965
00:38:07,177 --> 00:38:10,263
-I want to talk… [SIGHS]
-MAN: Tickets, please.

966
00:38:10,347 --> 00:38:12,891
-Sorry. I got to…
-MAN: Lady, what are you doing?

967
00:38:12,975 --> 00:38:15,518
-WOMAN: There's a line!
-MIDGE: Mama, I really need…

968
00:38:15,602 --> 00:38:17,354
Oy.

969
00:38:17,438 --> 00:38:19,522
ROSE: Miriam, I don't understand!

970
00:38:19,606 --> 00:38:22,192
How are you here if you were in Prague

971
00:38:22,276 --> 00:38:24,861
-this morning?
-I decided to come home early!

972
00:38:24,945 --> 00:38:27,906
-ROSE: Why?
-Because they told me to!

973
00:38:27,990 --> 00:38:29,866
-The Czechoslovakians?
-MIDGE: No!

974
00:38:29,950 --> 00:38:32,452
-Was the tour canceled?
-MIDGE: No!

975
00:38:32,536 --> 00:38:34,412
-Just me!
-ROSE: What?

976
00:38:34,496 --> 00:38:37,165
I said something onstage
that they didn't like,

977
00:38:37,249 --> 00:38:39,793
so they fired me. I was fired!

978
00:38:39,877 --> 00:38:40,919
-No!
-MOISHE: What?

979
00:38:41,003 --> 00:38:42,545
What did you say? What did she say?

980
00:38:42,629 --> 00:38:44,005
Oh, Miriam, how awful.

981
00:38:44,089 --> 00:38:46,174
-What did you say onstage?
-MIDGE: Just jokes!

982
00:38:46,258 --> 00:38:47,300
Very funny jokes,

983
00:38:47,384 --> 00:38:49,010
which I must point out
was the job description,

984
00:38:49,094 --> 00:38:51,429
but they got mad and
dropped me from the tour.

985
00:38:51,513 --> 00:38:54,474
At the airport. On the tarmac.

